			<h4>Anti-fraud Policy</h4>
	        	<p>A government issued photo ID and the credit card or the debit card used to complete the transaction for any order must be present when the customer is picking up the order. Any pick-up order without a valid photo ID and the credit card or the debit card that matches the one used for the immediate transaction shall be forfeited. No food shall be released in such case. This measure is enforced to prevent credit card fraud. </p>
	        <h4>Availability of food</h4>
	        	<p>Some food may suddenly become out of stock, although we always strive to give customers the best accuracy about items' availability. If such issue should occur, we would notify you with options to either cancel the item or change it to some other items we provide.</p>
	        <h4>Allergy disclaimer</h4> <p>It is customer's responsibility to expressively and clearly notify the restaurant staff about any allergy customer may have at the time of ordering or immediately afterward. This Nayada Thai Cuisine Website may or may not state any allergen that might be harmful to customer. Some allergens are not listed. You are here by release Nayada Thai Cuisine and its affiliate including Ittigorn Tradussadee of any liability regarding allergy symptom or sickness caused by consuming food from the restaurant.</p>
	        <h4>Food pictures</h4> <p>Food pictures on Nayada Thai Cuisine Website are for illustration purposes only and may not be accurate. There are many choices for types of meat and other options. Each option may cost differently. Type of meat visible in the picture does not mean that it is the default kind of met for that particular dish. The ingredients, garnishing, seasoning and overall appearance may look different depending on various factors. However, we strive to notify you of any change if it is significant and may provide you with alternative options. </p>
	        <h4>Policy regarding free items</h4>
	        	<p>We provide some condiments and utensils such as soy sauce and chopsticks free of charge. However, we reserve the right to limit the quantity of these free items regardless of how many has been added into order.</p>
		        <ul>
		        	<li>No more than 1 count of any condiment per one dish valued $1.00 to $5.99.</li>
		            <li>No more than 3 counts of any condiment (same type or combined) per one dish valued $6.00 or more.</li>
					<li>No more than 1 set of utensils per one dish valued $1.00 to $5.99.</li>
		            <li>No more than 2 sets of utensils per one dish valued $6.00 or more.</li>
		            <li>No more than 3 paper plates per one dish valued $6.00 or more.</li>
		            <li>No condiments or utensils are given unless requested expressively by customer.</li>
				</ul>
				<p>We hope that you would approve this policy as it would help us keep our cost low, which in turn enables us to keep providing you reasonable-priced food.</p>

